		<td><b>VGM player</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I decided to write a VGM player for the Gameboy.
<br />
<br />You can download it and the source code <a href="http://jiggawatt.org/badc0de/dmvgm-1.zip" class="postlink">here</a>
<br />And you can see/hear it in action <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oa4KlDeOoQQ" class="postlink">here</a>
<br />
<br />It obviously doesn't cover all the chips supported by the VGM format. Only the SN76489 is emulated (used in Sega Master System and Game Gear). 
<br />
<br />Since the waveform channel on the Gameboy only has 4 different volume settings it'll probably sound weird in some songs. Loading new waveforms dynamically to simulate 16 volume settings didn't seem like a good option.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


